## Email path

1. Save to Firestore → 2. `mail` collection doc → 3. Trigger Email extension → 4. optional direct SMTP

Recipients: `info@carlmanuel.com`, `carllouismanuel09@gmail.com`

**SMTP:** Gmail App Password only — `smtps://user:APP_PASSWORD@smtp.gmail.com:465` in `functions/.env` and extension config.

## `src/mapping.js`

Add prod + dev emulator URLs for every new HTTPS function. After deploy, verify prod URL from `firebase deploy` output.

## Deploy

```bash
cd functions && npm run deploy
```

Syncs `src/external-config.js` into `functions/` automatically.

## CORS (`applyCorsHeaders` / per-function origins)

Must include: `carlmanuel.com`, `www.carlmanuel.com`, `carlxaeron.github.io`, `localhost:3000`.

## Do not

- Commit `functions/.env` or extension `*.env` with secrets
- Leave temporary admin/export endpoints deployed without auth
- Use Gmail login password in SMTP URI (requires App Password)
